news.title: Nagpur: NIT yet to cancel lease, take back 16 plots even after CM withdraws order
news.para: NIT officials also said letters have been issued to the stamps and registration department not to execute any sale or lease or any type of deeds related to the 16 plots.

news.title: Property tax defaulters to lose water connections in Chandigarh
news.para: Over 2,300 residential properties owe Rs 4 crore tax to the MC. Arecent survey of the MC had revealed that posh areas of the northern part are the biggest defaulters in residential category.

news.title: Tamil Nadu housing board to tie up with private firms, construct homes at 12 places
news.para: After chairing a consultation meeting with flat owners of Singanallur housing unit, the minister said that the department will roll out the joint venture model to construct 960 flats in Coimbatore.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body gets 30% more in building plan charge in 2022
news.para: The GVMC realised 208 crore revenue by approving these plans in 2022. There is more than 30% increase in its revenue compared to the 150 crore that it could gain through building plan approval charges in 2021. The GVMC received 6,144 applications in 2021.

news.title: Audit led to vacating of 11 lakh sq ft space in I&B arms across 20 cities: Anurag Thakur
news.para: Thakur said a space audit and efficient management of buildings carried out as part of the Swachh Bharat Abhiyan also led to earnings of about Rs 22 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue minister agrees to reduce freehold charges to 2% of ready reckoner
news.para: Patil also gave his consent to reduce charges to be paid after renewal of lease. He also approved to bring down penal charges along with issuance of necessary clarification regarding charges of premium lease holders.

news.title: Madras HC upholds property tax hike in Chennai and Coimbatore
news.para: Both the corporations have been directed to ensure that their websites are kept robust and grievance mechanisms are put in place to enable all property tax assesses to seek clarifications regarding any aspect of property tax assessments.

news.title: Apple India renews lease for 52,000 sq ft flexible office space in Bengaluru
news.para: Apple India will operate out of the executive centre Safina Towers office in Bengaluru and will pay a rent of ₹1.42 crore per month, the sales deed mentioned.

news.title: Last date for depositing property tax extended to January 31: Haryana CM
news.para: The entire interest will be waived if the property tax is deposited by December 31, while a 50-per cent waiver will be given on depositing it by January 31.

news.title: New sand policy by January 15: Maharashtra Revenue Minister
news.para: Replying to a calling attention motion in assembly, revenue minister Radhakrishna Vikhe Patil said the issue of sand smuggling is big and the offenders were getting political patronage.

news.title: Kanpur: 50 beneficiaries get registry papers under PMAY
news.para: In the programme organized under the direction of KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh, the authorities gave registry papers of flats to around 50 beneficiaries of Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana.

news.title: Goldbricks Infrastructure cuts water supply from well, 470 flat owners face scarcity
news.para: There have been many issues between the flat owners and the developer since nearly a decade. The latest incident is likely to escalate the tension.

news.title: Mohali civic body exceeds property tax target by Rs 1.9 crore
news.para: The target collection of property tax announced in the budget allocated for the 2022-23 fiscal, as approved by the Punjab government for Mohali MC, was Rs 22 crore.

news.title: Complete distribution of permanent title deeds by January 2023: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: Taking stock of the distribution of title deeds at a review meeting of the scheme held at his Tadepalli camp office on Monday, the chief minister directed the officials to complete the distribution of title deeds by January 2023.

news.title: Indore collector orders strict action against illegal colonies
news.para: The collector, in the last time-limit meeting of this calendar year, asked all officials and employees to work for public welfare with positive attitude, thinking and enthusiasm in 2023 and take a pledge to ensure speedy resolution of pending work and bring transparency in their working.
